HEADWORD: Parturifacient
<hw>Par*tu`ri*fa"cient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>parturire</ets> to desire to bring forth + <ets>facere</ets> to
make.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A medicine tending to cause
parturition, or to give relief in childbearing.</def>
